b'When he was working as a civil servant, investment professional Richard Hall saw firsthand the hardships people face when they don\xe2\x80\x99t have adequate resources. That\xe2\x80\x99s why he decided to become a sovereign credit analyst. In this role he seeks investment opportunities in countries around the globe that help provide communities with more stability. #RigorousResearch #NotesFromTheRoad'

b'While digging in our corporate archive, we found a brochure from the 90s called: It\xe2\x80\x99s Tuesday at T. Rowe Price. The brochure may be a few decades old, but many of the ideas it conveys hold true today. For example, we still use the same strategic investing approach. From visiting companies onsite, to meeting with senior management, we do what it takes to find optimal investment opportunities for our clients. #FromTheArchives #RigorousResearch'

b'When our former CEO, Jim Kennedy (center), was Head of Equity Research, he would often participate in research visits like the one shown here in 1987. Meeting the company\xe2\x80\x99s employees and managers helped him gain a deeper understanding of day-to-day operations and enabled his team to make better-informed decisions about investing in the company, which is why we still conduct these visits today. #FromTheArchives #RigorousResearch'
